The Commission of Inquiry into allegations of State Capture is under way in Johannesburg. The commission is still hearing evidence related to law enforcement agencies. Former Police Minister Nathi Nhleko is back in the hot seat. Yesterday, he denied that he interfered with the work of the Independent Police Investigative Directorate (IPID) in the matter of the rendition of Zimbabwean citizens in 2010. Below is the live stream of the proceedings: 